  "abstract": "\"GIS Appl icat ion in Cropping System Analysis - Case Studies in Asia\" is a\r\nproduct of the hands-on training program for scientists f rom Asian national\r\nagricultural research systems (NARS) on the use of geographic informat ion\r\nsystem (GIS) in analysis of cropping systems. The main objective of this\r\ntraining program was to pave a progressive path towards greater\r\nunderstanding and use of GIS for meaningful interpretat ion of various\r\ndatasets. This publication contains an overview and methodologies of GIS\r\nsoftware. Participants f rom Bangladesh, India, Nepal , and Sri Lanka analyzed\r\ndatasets on rice-wheat and legumes using various GIS tools. The individual\r\ncase studies showed changed scenario in crop productivity, diseases, and\r\npests. A few case studies dealt wi th thematic mapping for constraints analysis.",
